commitmsg:
Checkpointing work on relative build/test times (comparative)

Currently hidden while I work on more pressing things

Initial work at converting to use flot + related cleanup

Currently only overall build & test turnaround uses flot, rest still using
highcharts

Fix some minor bugs in the new routing code

* Root didn't work
* Submit another 'is this build faster?' link didn't work
Restore accidentally deleted highcharts.js

Make different aspects of dashboard linkable

(using the fantastic sugarskull library)
Quick note on where to look up highcharts licensing
Fix link back to root
Remove test-only code

Improved "is this build faster" emails

* Show summary of how this build did compared to mean
* Nicer formatting

Make tree an "option" rather than freeform text

Really the only options we want are mozilla-central and try
Give instructions on running server in test mode
Fill in more stuff in settings.cfg.example
Add a README with installation instructions
Preserve arguments, use exec with convenience scripts

We need to use BeautifulSoup 3.2.0

4.0 (the default downloaded from PyPi as of this writing) doesn't work.
Fix add-job script to actually work

Update is my build faster processing to use jgriffin's new stuff

* We now process a mean and standard deviation of a series of recent builds.
* We display a list of highlighted test times where the revision being
tested differs by more than 2* the standard deviation.

Reorganize project and add a bootstrap script

Will hopefully make building/testing/hacking on this less of a
pain
Move graphs.js to gofaster.js
Add some contact information to welcome screen

First stab at an "is this build faster?" request tool

Fill out a form with the details of your try submission, get
some stats in the mail with the results. Easier than having to
install all the dependencies locally and negotiating a connection
to our elasticsearch server.
More minor cleanup of index page

Update welcome text a bit

No longer need to warn about charts taking a long time to load, link to wiki
page describing project.

Win7/WinXP tests should be win32 datapoints for overall build+test turnaround

Before we were treating them as seperate categories in and of themselves,
which was silly. Also rename "build pool turnaround" to "overall build
and test turnaround", more clear what it means.
Cache pickled file in memory, update only when changed

Add a little script to fetch and process live CSV

The intention being that it'll be run daily from a cron job

Use an absolute path to the pickled data

The rest of the app seems to require that, no sense in complicating things
Don't actually need to import JSON anymore

Adapt to using live data

* Ignore datapoints more than 30 days old
* Expect a header describing the fields in the CSV

Add a script to preparse the csv into a pickled file, use it

5000% speed improvement! (or thereabouts)

Also, remove the buildfaster data from html/. We'll dump all of that
in the server/data directory.
Simplify the remainder of the handler methods
Simplify to_seconds routine somewhat
Consolidate logic to parse CSV file into a single function, use everywhere

Consolidate and simplify logic to generate turnaround json

Saves about 1 second
temporary commenting out the mochitests dash
organizations
first commit

Bug 927664 - Add deploy.sh to the repo; r=wlach
Bug 927664 - Add 'bin/unit2-2.6' and 'lib64/' to .gitignore; r=wlach
Bug 932890 - Call the correct API endpoints, to avoid 303 redirects every time; r=wlach
Bug 926868 - Update fetch-and-process-builddata.sh to use builddata.pub.build.mozilla.org instead of build.m.o; r=wlach
Comment out isthisbuildfaster link for now, it's not working

Merge pull request #1 from wlach/master

Some minor changes

Add note about which builds are included in E2E calculations

Since this question has come up twice now. :)

Remove annoying step of copying over the server configuration

We can just copy over the default in bootstrap.sh
Make runserver.sh chatter make a bit more sense
Merge https://github.com/jonallengriffin/gofaster_dashboard
Add some links to bugzilla from the dashboard homescreen
Update script for pgo buildtype
Remove bullet for revision, add start time to build chart list

Make the buildchart list a little more sane: remove uid from the display, use standard 12-digit commit strings, group jobs together that are run on the same commit, and use long builder names for the lost job description.
Use builder_name instead of suitename to exclude duplicates
merge
Use first 12 chars of revision when filtering for first build per rev
Use first 12 chars of revision when filtering for first build per rev

Add option for "local-only" mode for fetching/processing builddata

Handy when debugging the same data set repeatedly

Minor changes to build summaries and end-to-end time calculations

* Time for build/test should be based on the time the first event is
submitted, not when the first build starts.
* Only use first job submitted for that revision (should exclude nightlies)
when calculating end-to-end times.
Put build id in URL for getting build data
Use sugarskull for all routing in buildchart view
Minor cleanups from code review with jgriffin

Fix "null" strings when displaying buildcharts on webkit-based browsers

These browsers render null text as "null", so do a check before drawing the
text.

Minor cleanups from code review with jgriffin

These browsers render null text as "null", so do a check before drawing the
text.
Use builder name in description of builds for buildcharts

A few more enhancements to the build detail view

* Make build details linkable
* Better/more descriptive error when no build details available
Increase build step inclusion threshold to 2.5%

Add a threshold of 1% for a build step to appear in the pie chart

Removes a bit of noise

Add a bit of explanatory text to the build chart view

Explaining:
* Why tests start before builds are done
* That you can click on builds to get a more detailed breakdown
First patch at getting build details from build charts

Sort OSes in graph alphabetically

Ensures consistent coloring, etc.

Modify run script for server so ctrl-c always works

Some trapping action. Crude but effective!

Add a show outliers option, related refactoring

Now have the option of hiding outliers. Refactored stuff to make it easier
to add options like this.
Remove mochitest and turnaround handlers

Minimum y (time) value on graphs should be 0

Gives a better idea of where we're really at.
Forgot to update code to return buildchart events for new range stuff, fix
Make logo link work again

Allow selecting range of dates for graph time periods

As opposed to only showing the last 30, let the user select the
last 60, or even all time. Making this happen in a reasonable way
involved some fairly intensive refactoring of the entire site.
Consolidate graph-plotting logic into a single function
Remove obsolete description at top of main js file

Remove turnaround and slow mochitest code

It's bitrotting to hell, and there's always git history

Consolidate and simplify graph divs into a template

(first step in refactoring graphs to be easier to extend)
Add my changes to flot hiddengraphs, makes UI a bit easier to manage
Don't include non-existent gantt chart js in index
Update docs

Stop autogenerating utility scripts which don't vary per installation

Less confusing that way
Show wait times in build charts, alter display to accomodate them

Include flot highlighter plugin (required by gantt charts)

We aren't really using it for anything, but we get a bunch of javascript
errors if we don't include it.

Use timestamps for storing submitted time

Convert to YY-MM-DD only when needed. We'll use this for showing the
submitted time in the buildcharts.

Generate a script to grab/process the CSV instead of putting one in the tree

This way our script can be programmed to use the virtualenv and we can put
it in the more convenient bin/ directory.

Filter out tests that have already occurred when parsing csv

Specifically, tests run more than once. We can do this by looking
at the new "suitename" column and keeping a hash of those that
we've already seen per build.

Import the test suitename and use it in the buildcharts

Allows us to see which particular test suites are taking a long time in the
build charts.
Don't try to import exporting.js (it was part of highcharts)

Use updated templeton syntax for json decorator + own clone of templeton

This allows us to make improvements to templeton and use them immediately.
Use recommended templeton handler syntax
Utility script to start/stop server
Fix copyright attribution

Remove javascript to show slow mochitests

Broken by recent changes, can always bring it back later
Take out some stray console.logs from the buildchart renderer
Fix time taken summary on buildchart
Link to wiki page from README
Link to github project on main page
Entirely replace highcharts.js with flot

New mode to show average end-to-end times

The actual metric we're trying to get down to 2!

Hide turnaround view

It doesn't seem to be a useful metric, but we'll keep it around for a bit
just in case.
Add end to end times per OS to dashboard
Add license blocks
Remove duplicate unused script
Show the last job to complete in the list of buildcharts

Render buildcharts using flot

Using a slightly modified version of Juergen Marsch's gantt char flot plugin
Fix location of buildchart.js

Refinements to display of bootchart list

Sorted in reverse chronological order, gives a hint of how long the
build took.
Fix heights of divs by using containers appropriately

First cut at support for rendering a "build chart" of build/test events

Hopefully this will help us narrow down what's going on.
